# вљ™пёЏ Installation

## Clone Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/AI-Resume-Screener.git

cd AI-Resume-Screener
```

---

## Backend Setup

```bash
cd backend

python -m venv venv

# Windows
venv\Scripts\activate

# Linux/Mac
source venv/bin/activate

pip install -r requirements.txt
```

Run the backend

```bash
uvicorn main:app --reload
```

Backend runs at

```
http://127.0.0.1:8000
```

Swagger Documentation

```
http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs
```

---

## Frontend Setup

```bash
cd frontend

npm install

npm run dev
```

Frontend runs at

```
http://localhost:5173
```

---

# рџ“– API Endpoints

## Upload Resume

```
POST /upload/upload
```

Uploads and extracts text from a resume PDF.

---

## Rank Candidates

```
POST /ranking/rank
```

Inputs

- Job Description PDF
- Multiple Resume PDFs

Returns

- Candidate Rankings
- AI Scores
- Extracted Information

---

## Get Candidates

```
GET /candidates
```

Returns all stored candidates.

---

## Get Candidate

```
GET /candidates/{id}
```

Returns a single candidate.

---

## Delete Candidate

```
DELETE /candidates/{id}
```

Deletes a candidate.

---

## Analytics

```
GET /analytics
```

Returns

- Average Score
- Skill Distribution
- Education Distribution
- Score Distribution
- Total Candidates

---

# рџ“Љ Candidate Evaluation

Each resume receives:

- Semantic Similarity Score
- Skill Match Score
- Education Score
- Experience Score
- Eligibility Score
- Final AI Score

Candidates are automatically ranked based on the Final Score.

---



# рџљЂ Deployment

The application can be deployed using:

- Render (Backend)
- Vercel (Frontend)

or as a single Render Web Service by serving the built React application through FastAPI.

